    ðŸ”¹ `newgrp -` --> ðŸ”™ Returns you to the group you were previously using. This is done by setting `$LOGNAME` and re-logging you in.

ðŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ newgrp mygroup

    ðŸ”¹ Changes the current group to "mygroup". If you are not a member of "mygroup", the command will fail.

    $ newgrp -

    ðŸ”¹ Returns you to the previous group. You will be prompted for your password.

